# Arm64 Container Launch Fix — Summary

## Root Causes Found & Fixed

### 1. ⚠️ CRITICAL: `WineInfo.fromIdentifier()` Architecture Parsing Bug
**File:** [WineInfo.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/WineInfo.java#L117-L166)

**Bug:** When a wine version identifier (e.g., `proton-9.0-arm64ec`) had a matching `ContentProfile`, the method stripped the architecture suffix (`-arm64ec`) before regex matching:
- Input: `proton-9.0-arm64ec` → stripped to `proton-9.0`
- Regex failed to match (no architecture part) → fell back to `MAIN_WINE_VERSION` (`x86_64`)
- **Result:** ALL arm64ec containers were silently treated as x86_64 at runtime

**Additionally:** The fix initially had a double `matcher.find()` call bug — `Matcher.find()` is stateful and calling it twice would advance past the match. Fixed by storing the result in a `boolean matched` variable.

**Fix:** Preserved the original identifier for regex matching while still using the stripped version for content profile path lookup.

### 2. Hardcoded x86_64 in Auto-Container Creation
**File:** [UnifiedActivity.kt](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/UnifiedActivity.kt#L1416-L1427)

**Bug:** [launchSteamGame()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/UnifiedActivity.kt#1377-1480) hardcoded `"proton-9.0-x86_64"` when auto-creating containers, meaning any new container created automatically would always be x86_64.

**Fix:** Now uses the wine version from the first existing container if available, falling back to `MAIN_WINE_VERSION` otherwise.

### 3. Emulator Selection Not Enforced in Per-Game Settings  
**Files:**
- [ShortcutSettingsDialog.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/ShortcutSettingsDialog.java#L188-L208)
- [ContainerDetailFragment.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/ContainerDetailFragment.java#L1238-L1254)

**Bug:** Users could manually select wrong emulators (e.g., Box64 on arm64ec containers). The UI didn't strictly enforce the architecture-emulator pairing.

**Fix:** Both emulator spinners are now **disabled** and **forced** to the correct value:
- **Arm64EC containers:** Both emulators locked to FEXCore (index 0)
- **x86_64 containers:** Both emulators locked to Box64 (index 1)

### 4. Runtime Emulator Override in GuestProgramLauncherComponent
**File:** [GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/xenvironment/components/GuestProgramLauncherComponent.java#L358-L374)

**Enhancement:** Added a runtime safety net that forces the correct emulator regardless of what's stored in container/shortcut settings. Even if a container has a stale/wrong emulator value, the launch will use the correct one based on `wineInfo.isArm64EC()`. Also added comprehensive debug logging for the entire emulator selection flow.

## Build Status
✅ **BUILD SUCCESSFUL** — All changes compile cleanly with no errors.

## How the Fix Works End-to-End

```
User launches game on Arm64 container
  → XServerDisplayActivity reads container wine version ("proton-9.0-arm64ec")
  → WineInfo.fromIdentifier() correctly parses arch as "arm64ec" ✅ (was broken)
  → wineInfo.isArm64EC() returns TRUE
  → GuestProgramLauncherComponent.start():
      → extractEmulatorsDlls() (FEXCore WoW64 DLLs)
  → GuestProgramLauncherComponent.execGuestProgram():
      → Forces emulator to "FEXCore" ✅
      → Sets HODLL=libwow64fex.dll
      → Launches wine directly (no box64 wrapper)
```

